article.headline: W. Carolina 66, Bradley 65
article.story: CULLOWHEE, N.C. -- Mike Williams scored 16 points and Western Carolina used a late run to beat Bradley 66-65 on Tuesday night. The Catamounts (4-4), who were down by as many as 12, trailed 58-47 with 9:51 to play. They then outscored the Braves 14-2 to take the lead for good, 61-60. Richie Gordon, who finished with 13 points, capped the spurt on two free throws with 2:43 to play. The Catamounts went 5 for 6 from the free-throw line the rest of the way. Andrew Warren hit a 3-pointer for Bradley with 1 second left for the final margin. Keaton Cole added 14 points for Western Carolina and Tawaski King chipped in 10 rebounds. Western Carolina outrebounded the Braves 44-27 and the Catamounts scored 10 of their 11 second-chance points in the second half. Warren finished with 22 points and Dodie Dunson added 14 for Bradley (4-3), which lost its third in a row.
